@startuml
title Stanford Quadruped Learning Overview\n(shared core reused by robot and simulation runtimes)

skinparam componentStyle rectangle
skinparam packageStyle rectangle
skinparam shadowing false
skinparam defaultFontName Consolas
skinparam wrapWidth 240
skinparam maxMessageSize 220
skinparam linetype ortho
skinparam ArrowThickness 2
skinparam nodesep 100
skinparam ranksep 120
left to right direction

caption Read this figure as: runtime entry -> command / observation adapters -> shared locomotion core -> actuation / environment closure.\nThe same Controller / Gait / Swing / Stance / IK stack is reused by both run_robot.py and sim/run_floating_base.py.

package "1. Real Robot Runtime" {
  component "run_robot.py\nmain()" as RobotEntry
  component "JoystickInterface\nsrc/JoystickInterface.py" as Joy
  component "IMU\nsrc/IMU.py" as IMU
  component "HardwareInterface\npupper/HardwareInterface.py" as HW
  component "Physical robot\nservos + links + ground" as Plant
  component "Robot observation bus" as RobotObsBus

  RobotEntry -[hidden]down-> Joy
  Joy -[hidden]right-> IMU
  IMU -[hidden]right-> RobotObsBus
  RobotObsBus -[hidden]right-> HW
  HW -[hidden]right-> Plant
}

package "2. Shared Contracts" {
  database "Configuration\npupper/Config.py" as Config
  component "Command\nsrc/Command.py" as Command
  database "State\nsrc/State.py" as State
  component "Command / state bus" as SharedBus

  Config -[hidden]down-> Command
  Command -[hidden]right-> State
  State -[hidden]down-> SharedBus
}

package "3. Shared Locomotion Core" {
  component "Controller.run()\nsrc/Controller.py" as Controller
  component "GaitController\nphase / contacts\nsrc/Gaits.py" as Gait
  component "StanceController\nsupport-leg update\nsrc/StanceController.py" as Stance
  component "SwingController\nRaibert touchdown + swing height\nsrc/SwingLegController.py" as Swing
  component "four_legs_inverse_kinematics()\npupper/Kinematics.py" as IK
  component "Desired joint target bus" as JointBus

  Controller -[hidden]down-> Gait
  Gait -[hidden]right-> Stance
  Stance -[hidden]right-> Swing
  Swing -[hidden]right-> IK
  IK -[hidden]down-> JointBus
}

package "4. Simulation Runtime" {
  component "sim/run_floating_base.py\nmain() + run loop" as SimEntry
  component "TaskScheduler\nsim/task_scheduler.py" as Scheduler
  component "TaskCommandSource\nsim/sim_robot.py" as CmdSource
  component "apply_feedback()\nsim/run_floating_base.py" as Feedback
  component "SimObservationInterface + SimIMU\nsim/sim_robot.py" as SimObs
  component "SimHardwareInterface\nPD torque tracker\nsim/sim_robot.py" as SimHW
  component "MuJoCo\nMjModel + MjData" as MJ
  component "Viewer / plots / telemetry" as Viz

  SimEntry -[hidden]down-> Scheduler
  Scheduler -[hidden]right-> CmdSource
  CmdSource -[hidden]right-> Feedback
  Feedback -[hidden]down-> SimObs
  SimObs -[hidden]right-> SimHW
  SimHW -[hidden]right-> MJ
  MJ -[hidden]right-> Viz
}

RobotEntry --> Joy : read gamepad
IMU --> RobotObsBus : orientation
Plant --> RobotObsBus : body / foot / contact\n(physical world)
Joy --> Command : vx vy yaw\nheight pitch roll\ntrot / hop / activate
RobotObsBus --> State : measured state

SimEntry --> Scheduler : mode / settle / task sequence
Scheduler --> CmdSource : current task step
CmdSource --> Feedback : nominal command
State --> Feedback : measured pose / velocity
Feedback --> Command : compensated command
SimEntry --> SimObs : create adapters
SimObs --> State : measured state
JointBus --> SimHW : joint targets
SimHW --> MJ : PD torque + mj_step()
MJ --> SimObs : sensors + kinematics
MJ --> Viz : viewer data

Config --> SharedBus : gait + robot params
Command --> SharedBus : desired motion
State --> SharedBus : measured / estimated state
SharedBus --> Controller : controller inputs

Controller --> Gait : phase index / contact mode
Controller --> Stance : stance legs
Controller --> Swing : swing legs
Gait --> Stance : support phase
Gait --> Swing : swing proportion
Stance --> IK : stance foot targets
Swing --> IK : swing foot targets
IK --> JointBus : 12 joint angles
JointBus --> HW : target joint angles
HW --> Plant : servo commands
Plant --> State : next physical response

@enduml
